  {
    "section_type": "discussion",
    "type": "minutes_chunk",
    "document_type": "minutes",
    "document_subtype": "officer",
    "source_file": "June 19, 2025 _ Officer Meeting.txt",
    "role": "N/A",
    "person": "N/A",
    "content": "* VP External - Should we bid for PM 2027?\n* The bid would either be placed at FYIC or CALE\n* The main expense would be accomodation\n* This can be mostly covered with delegate fees\n* We need to consider whether we have enough engagement as a society\n* 101 week will be a good opportunity to gauge this\n* We need to look for first and second year students who might be interested in joining the organizing committee, since they will still be around when this conference is held\n* We need a dedicated team to avoid the issues we’ve had with organising previous conferences, this is more important than the finances of the society as a determining factor as to whether this is feasible\n* President: Finish your budgets soon\n* President: Retreat\n* Next week!\n* Fill out the spreadsheet in advance so that we’re not scrambling last minute\n* Chair: VP Social is not in Ottawa which is a violation of the requirements for the position\n* This will be raised at the BoD meeting on Sunday\n* Received advice that it’s especially important for the VP Social to be there for August\n* The Presidents knew about this but did not raise it with the team\n* We need to be more open about these things in the future\n* Internal: absent officers at meetings\n* Some officers have been excused\n* One of the VPs hasn’t showed up to any meetings so far\n* President will follow up with a warning\n* Internal: My emails are going to spam\n* Maybe reach out to uOttawa Engineering IT helpdesk or look into our DNS config",
    "meeting_date": "2025-06-19",
    "meeting_date_display": "Jun 19, 2025"
  },
